                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know the drug companies have to recoup money for investment in finding new medicines but maybe, just maybe, they could lower drug prices instead of charging a premium for US customers. Why is it that medicines purchased from Canada are deemed unsafe when they are made by and exported from the US by American companies? Why are medicines made by companies in other parts of the world from the same labs that ship medicine to the US but shipped outside of the US considered unsafe? It's called big business and politics. The companies that makes medicines and drugs have a stranglehold on the distribution of drugs to the US and the prices we in the US pay are astronomically higher than in other countries. Politicians with kickbacks from big business equals screwed John Doe.
<br />

<br />
I am glad that they are at least taking steps into making medicine cheaper for those who need it most but it's no substitute for giving fair prices. Instead the drug companies KNOW they have a captive audience and can price gouge to their hearts content.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">On the other hand, if your reaction to something I say boils down to "You didn't choose MY side, make MY choice," well, you're not looking for information, you're looking for someone to tell you how smart you are thinking the way you do. --</span> <span style="font-weight: bold">Ed Stroligo</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
