                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Why do drugs cost more in this country?  Here is one of the reasons.  Cost of doing business in the USA.  It cost the drug companies more money to run trials to get it through the FDA...many times a drug is already released in Europe or other parts of the world.  A drug manufacturer has to take out a malpractice insurance policy for each drug made to protect it from litigation.  Silicone implants bankrupted Dupont when the breast implants cases went to class action...even though scientific research later on did not substantiate the claim that leaking silicone caused all those ailments.
<br />

<br />
By the time a drug is successfully launched here, it doesnt have a long patent life left.
<br />

<br />
We live in a society where anyone can sue.  It is a priviledge....but it doesnt come cheap.
<br />

<br />
Tort reform is being actively debated and we all should learn more about both sides.  But why do drugs cost more here...it cost more to do business here.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
