                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Juwel,
<br />

<br />
I am sorry to see that the silicone migrated from the implant site in your mother; however, there have been multiple studies not done by the drug companies but by national goverments and institutions about silicone breast implants.  Here is a link with citations.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.silicone-review.gov.uk/history/index.htm" target="_blank">http://www.silicone-review.gov.uk/history/index.htm</a>
<br />

<br />
As you can see, the US goverment (FDA and American Medical Association), Canadien goverment, UK through independent panels and the French government have all reviewed the impact of silicone.
<br />

<br />
As for extra cost, class actions suites can bankrupt a company not just cost it money.  Merck has already lost 30 - 40% of its value since Vioxx was withdrawn and it hasnt even entered litigation yet.
<br />

<br />
All drugs have adverse effects.  It is estimated that non steriodal anti inflammatories have about 0.4% increase in heart risk.  For a patient with severe Rheumatoid arthritis, who couldnt function if they didnt take that medicine, it was a no brainer...they would take the risk so that they could move that day without pain.  But when 20 million people in this country take NSAIDs...0.4% could be hundreds of thousands of people.  We have drugs that increase cancer...estrogen...and yet it is acceptable for every woman to decide whether their hot flashes or post menopausal symptoms warrant taking such risk.  As with any drug, every individual has to decide whether the benefit of the drug outweighs potential risks....because there is no drug that is without risk.
<br />

<br />
Skil</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
