		<td class="row2" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="nav"><a href="#top" class="nav">Back to top</a></span></td>
		<td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="bottom" nowrap="nowrap"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" height="18" width="18"><tr><td valign="absbottom" nowrap="nowrap"><span class="gensmall"><a href="./profile.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1982"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_profile.gif" border="0" alt="View user's profile" title="View user's profile" /></a>&nbsp;</span></td></tr></table></td>
	</tr>
        <tr>
                <td class="spaceRow" colspan="2" height="1"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/spacer.gif" alt="" width="1" height="1" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row1"><a name="93999"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Yakk</span></span></td>
                <td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a href="viewtopic.php?p=93999#93999"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Wed Jan 19, 2005 4:00 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td align="right" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=93999"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td></tr></table></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Somewhat facile. If a Canadian Doctor were to Ok the prescription of a drug without history and self confirmation of the diagnosis he would be struck off. (I'm not Canadian but their medical standards are similar to ours). Drugs really are just drugs most doctors will know that this variant of salbutamol, for eg, will have these different effects than that brand etc </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
If that patient where to come to Canada and become the Doctor's patient, I'd be ok with the Canadian Doctor perscribing drugs to the patient.
<br />

<br />
That isn't what is happening.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Gawd what an asininine statement. The thing is is that most people aren't taking a drug because they feel like it. They ar taking it because it is prescribed to treat /alleviate a specific condition.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Yes, they are taking it because they want to take it.  The alternative might be bad, but it is up to them if they want to pay the price.
<br />

<br />
The drug companies would love to be able to selectively price, like MIT does.  You set an extremely high price, and then you give 'discounts' based on means.
<br />

<br />
This allows you to capture all of the profit.  And for many drugs, people will be willing to morgage their homes for access.
<br />

<br />
The Canadian model is different.  It has other costs (less choice, etc), but it results in cheaper drugs.  American's trying to mooch off the Canadian model will do harm to Canadians.  As such, I do not want American's buying Canadian cheap perscriptions.  That will increase the cost to drug companies who agree to lower prices for selling drugs in Canada, and not benefit Canadians.
<br />

<br />
As I said, fix your own health system.  If you don't like the American health system, change it.  Or move to Canada.  Undermining the Canadian system to patch over problems with the American one isn't something Canadians need.
<br />

<br />
There are currently bills being proposed in many provinces to shut down the practice of cross-border perscription sales, and at least one Doctor is up for discipline because they where rubber stamping perscriptions in B.C.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
