<br />

<br />
But it's certainly relevant to purchasing medications across the border, because safeguards are not in place to prevent this. It's the potential for abuse that is a serious health concern and can be abused wholesale by the unethical. Lets not forget that some drugs are legal for medical use here that are not in the US and vice versa, pot probably being the most obvious. Canadians can purchase drugs more inexpensively because the government makes it happen for us, and there is no reason that the US can't have the same thing if they want it, but they don't because it hurts profits and for some incredible reason that's more important then quality of life to the majority of voting Americans.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />1010011010 - Binary of the Beast!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
